NASA SEWP PROCUREMENT NOTICE
============================

Dear SEWP Contract Holders,

The National Aeronautics and Space Administration (NASA) is seeking quotations 
for enterprise network infrastructure equipment under our SEWP V contract vehicle.

PROCUREMENT DETAILS:
-------------------
RFQ Number: NASA-2025-001
Issuing Office: NASA Goddard Space Flight Center
Project: Mission Critical Network Upgrade
Classification: Unclassified

TIMELINE:
---------
RFQ Issue Date: May 15, 2025
Questions Due: May 29, 2025 at 2:00 PM EDT
Quotes Due: June 12, 2025 at 4:00 PM EDT

TECHNICAL REQUIREMENTS:
----------------------
We require enterprise-grade networking equipment including:

1. Core Network Switches (Qty: 12)
   - 48-port Gigabit Ethernet
   - 10G uplink capabilities
   - Redundant power supplies
   - FIPS 140-2 Level 2 certification required

2. Edge Routers (Qty: 8) 
   - BGP routing capability
   - IPv6 support mandatory
   - Space-qualified components preferred
   - Security compliance: NIST 800-53

3. Wireless Access Points (Qty: 150)
   - Wi-Fi 6E standard
   - Federal security requirements
   - Centralized management system

SPECIAL REQUIREMENTS:
--------------------
- All equipment must be TAA compliant
- Security clearance may be required for installation
- CONUS manufacturing preference
- Energy Star certification required
- 24/7 technical support with 4-hour response time

DELIVERY REQUIREMENTS:
---------------------
Primary Delivery Location:
NASA Goddard Space Flight Center
8800 Greenbelt Road
Greenbelt, MD 20771

Secondary Locations:
- NASA Johnson Space Center, Houston, TX
- NASA Kennedy Space Center, FL

EVALUATION CRITERIA:
-------------------
This procurement will be evaluated using Lowest Price Technically Acceptable (LPTA) methodology.

Technical factors include:
- Compliance with all stated requirements
- Technical specifications and performance
- Past performance with federal agencies
- Delivery schedule adherence

